# gtc_v2_sim

Minimal GTC v2 case folder for running the ITG Cyclone base case as a
nonlinear electrostatic ion-temperature-gradient calculation with the zonal
mode enabled (`mode00=1`).

Build:

```sh
make
```

Run the default short nonlinear case:

```sh
./run_itg_cyclone_base_nonlinear_zonal.sh
```

Useful runtime overrides:

```sh
MPI_NP=10 MSTEP=1000 MSNAP=10 CASE_DIR=itg_run_1000 ./run_itg_cyclone_base_nonlinear_zonal.sh
```

Set `KEEP_RESTART=1` if you want to retain restart files. They are removed by
default to keep the case folder small.

Main outputs in the case directory:

- `history.out`: scalar and mode-amplitude history
- `sheareb.out`: zonal-flow/shearing diagnostics
- `snap*.out`: profile and field snapshots
- `summary.csv`: quick run summary
- `plots/`: generated figures when Python plotting dependencies are present
